--------------
1.1 "Licensor" means the copyright holder(s) or other rights holder(s) offering the Software
under this License.

1.2 "Software" means this version of the Palyra software made available by the Licensor under
this License, including source code, object code, build scripts, configuration, and repository
documentation that the Licensor includes in the licensed repository.

1.3 "You" means an individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

1.4 "Derivative Work" means any work based upon the Software for which Your modifications,
as a whole, would be protected by copyright law. For clarity, modifications, ports, adapters,
refactors, patches, extensions, and combinations that include any substantial portion of the
Software are Derivative Works.

1.5 "Distribute" means to provide, publish, make available, transfer, or otherwise convey a
copy of the Software or a Derivative Work to any third party, whether in source or object form,
including via source control platforms, package registries, container registries, downloads,
physical media, or network delivery.

1.6 "Professional Services" means bona fide human-delivered services such as consulting,
installation, configuration, integration, migration, customization, development, training,
operations support, troubleshooting, and maintenance for a specific customer.

1.7 "Dedicated Customer Deployment" means a deployment of the Software or a Derivative Work
that is prepared for, or operated solely for, a specifically identified customer or that
customer's affiliates, and is not offered as a shared, multi-tenant, or generally available
commercial service to unrelated third parties.

1.8 "Competitive Offering" means making the Software or a Derivative Work available to third
parties, for direct or indirect commercial advantage or monetary compensation, as or within a
product or service that:

(a) substitutes for the Software;

(b) substitutes for any product or service that the Licensor offers using the Software and that
exists when the applicable version of the Software is first made available under this License; or

(c) offers the same or substantially similar core functionality as the Software.

For clarity, a Competitive Offering includes selling, licensing, sublicensing, white-labeling,
OEM-ing, embedding, hosting, or managing the Software or a Derivative Work as a standalone,
general-purpose, or generally available commercial product or service. A Competitive Offering
does not include activity that is expressly permitted by Section 4.

