-------------------------------
3.1 License and Copyright Notices.
If You Distribute the Software or a Derivative Work, You must provide a copy of this License and
preserve all copyright, license, and attribution notices included in or with the Software,
except to the extent a notice must be updated to reflect Your own modifications.

3.2 Same License for Software Portions.
If You Distribute the Software or a Derivative Work, the Software and Derivative Work portions
must remain available under this License. You may not relicense those portions under different
terms or impose additional restrictions on recipients' rights in those portions under this
License. If You Distribute the Software or a Derivative Work as part of a larger work, You may
license the larger work under other terms, provided those other terms do not limit recipients'
rights under this License with respect to the Software and Derivative Work portions.

3.3 Mark Your Changes.
If You Distribute a Derivative Work, You must include prominent notices stating that You modified
the Software.

3.4 No Passing Off.
You may not remove, obscure, falsify, or misrepresent the origin of the Software. You may not
state or imply that the original Software was authored solely by You. You may identify,
copyright, and brand Your own modifications, but not in a way that hides the Licensor's authorship
